@yuslepukhin, the compressed model is about 246 MB, how to sharing for your easy access ?

For the Gemm operator, the const inputs B, C are from below zip file, and input A could be an arbitary [N * 512] float metrix
[Data.zip](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/files/6463928/Data.zip)

The result difference happens for 1 * 512 and N * 512 (where N > 1), for N  > 1, i.e. 2 * 512 and 3 * 512, the results are consistence.

@Distancehe are you computing this on CPU or CUDA, just to clarify. Also, what are you using to output text data? Can it be that python and C# codes simply print this differently with different number of significant digits and round this up at times? This is what it looks like from the output.
